title: Amaterasu 13
body:
1. SparkSql runner can read a dataframe from a previous action through AmaContext.
2. SparkSql runner can parse amacontext from user supplied query.
3. SparkSql can read/write data directly from parquet ,json, parquet, orm and text files. JDBC support will be added in future releases.
4. If no dataframe read format is specified by user, parquet is used as default file format to load data from previous actions.
5. Updated SQL parser to parse advanced queries.
